I've ordered the panang curry before from Thaiphoon and it was really good. My recent order however was another story entirely. The panang curry this time around had absolutely no flavor, I mean like none, it tasted like the chicken was simply thrown in a bat of coconut milk, and that's literally it. Needless to say I won't be ordering anything from Thaiphoon in the future.

I had a wonderful experience at this restaurant despite there being Plumbing issues. When my friend and I are arrived at the restaurant we noticed there were candles burning everywhere. At first I thought this was a nice touch but then I realize they were having problems with their bathroom and the candles were meant to mask any smells. Now this did not take away from the overall experience but I wanted to make note. The food was really good and our server was amazing! Once I lived in The Wyoming, hustled atop the hill behind the Hilton.  Dropped in at Taiphoon a couple of times a month when schedules were bad, no time to cook n or enough time to eat beyond a fav local. (mostly I went to, and met up with Rachel at the wonderful La Tomate after work then). Today, nostalgic, went back to Taiphoon in easy walking distance despite the COLD, and had my entree served up with HAIR in my food. No way that black colored hair was from my head these days! Bad shrimp appetizer, but entree with hair just shut me down. Called them over and said I would pay for my drink, but wound up even being charged with my over-fried appetizer too, and it likely had hair fried into it!   Told patron seated next to me, despite nearly empty restaurant, to watch out. Of course, her dripping nose six inches from me fed into my disappointment. Goodby Taiphoon, even if jou have expanded into a franchise and could be an easy alternative to mediocre food at the convention hotel, the Hilton.

Thaiphoon Wonderful Thai food! Like many of the other reviews, I think they have great food and great service. I often go there for the tom ka soup with chicken or shrimp, the pad Thai, pad see ew, or the duck over spinach. It's always super fresh and warm and the servers are very friendly. If you're in the mood for some great, wallet friendly Thai food, this is the place to go!

I don't understand all of these very good reviews. My party of four were all fairly unsatisfied by the curry here. The eggplant was undercooked, the curry was watery/sugary, and the tofu was spongy. I know that you have to be crazy to order cocktails at a Thai place like this, but DON'T! The drinks were absolutely terrible and the cocktail menu is a total lie. Each of us got a different tropical cocktail from the menu, which claimed they all had various fresh fruit juices and nice liquor. All four were pretty transparently Kool-Aid type mixes with cheap liquor. It was really obvious, and we paid like $12 for each one. Two of my friends couldn't even finish theirs because it was clearly just blue powder stirred into tequila. The decor is weird and the menus are laminated and trashy. Go elsewhere for Thai, this is some of the worst in DC.

Everyone knows the best Vietnamese in the area is in Arlington (Eden Center), and the best Korean is in Annandale.  But the clear winner for Thai is Thaiphoon in Dupont.  No one tries harder to create the perfect balance of flavor, from the Indian inspired spice infusion of their lemongrass chicken, to the tropically inspired green curry, their menu is a gastronomic wonderland.  The presentation is also top-notch, with dishes that seem prepared for a magazine shoot.  Day in and day out, this is the consistent best-in-class among the many restaurants vying for the palate of DC's most discerning Thai enthusiasts.

This place was really good.  I came with a large group (15) and they were able to accommodate my reservation, even though I had to move it by 30 min at the last minute.  They were very quick and efficient with the service. The food was tasty and very reasonably priced.  Would definitely organize a group event here again.
Good food... Okay service

The DC market is saturated with restaurants, including Thai food so it's common to expect good food with decent service.  My friends and I thought the dishes we chose were well done but the service we received from our waiter was horrible.  He kept rushing us with making our selection five minutes after we got our menu.  He did not appear friendly and was not communicative at all.  The impression we got was that he was either not happy working there or he was not well trained.  The restaurant was not that busy but It was ridiculous trying to flag him down to order another bowl of rice for our table.  My friend would have ordered another drink but decided that it was too much of a hassle.  It had been awhile since I came back to this restaurant and I now remember the reason why.  There's another Thai restaurant around the corner with much better service.  I recommend going there instead.
